"Recent developments in Ferguson involve ongoing protests and calls for justice for Mike Brown, with users sharing videos of daily events and footage of the police chief speaking with protesters on a Friday morning. There is a significant push for citizen journalism, with individuals seeking to livestream and tweet updates to inform the global public. Additionally, data highlights racial disparities in law enforcement, noting that while Black citizens comprise 67% of the population, they account for 86% of police stops, 92% of searches, and 93% of arrests."